did.head: Descriptive Summary
did.repository: Special Collections, Virginia Tech, Blacksburg, Va.
did.abstract: The collection contains individual or groups of issues of Virginia newspapers, organized by location and dating from the 1860s-1990s.

userestrict.head: Use Restrictions
userestrict.p: Permission to publish material from newspapers in the collection must be obtained from Special Collections, Virginia Tech.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Researchers wishing to cite this collection should include the following information: Virginia Newspaper Collection, Ms2012-034, Special Collections, Virginia Polytechnic Institute and State University, Blacksburg, Va.
Researchers may also wish to consult an appropriate style guide for citing articles within newspapers.

acqinfo.head: Acquisition Information
acqinfo.p: The newspapers in this collection have been donated to Special Collections over time. Additional materials may be added in the future.

processinfo.head: Processing Information
processinfo.p: An inventory of the newspapers was created during the summer of 2011. Description of the collection was completed in July 2012. Additional newspapers added in June 2017.

otherfindaid.head: Other Finding Aids
otherfindaid.p: A spreadsheet with information about specific holdings (titles, dates, volume and issue numbers, cities/towns of publication, and, when available, cost and editors) can be downloaded here. The spreadsheets allows for easy sorting by any category.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Content
scopecontent.p: This collection consists of individual issues of Virginia newspapers. In some cases, this is a single issue; in other cases, there may be multiple issues. Newspapers represent cities and towns throughout the Commonwealth and date from the start of the Civil War up through the 1990s.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: The physical collection is arranged alphabetically by city or town. The contents list below is organized by city or town and contains a list of paper titles in each box. The city or town of origination is included with the title. Under each title is a list of holdings. The general format is "date, volume, issue number." Some titles may only list dates or dates and volumes.
For ease of searching, a downloadable spreadsheet which can be sorted by city/town, title, date, issue, and other known information, can be found here.
